      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">A 36 years old pregnant female presents to the Pediatrics department for a regular visit for her 3 years old child with a trisomy which is responsible for the presenile Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease. You noticed that she is pregnant again and she replied that it is her 2<sup>nd</sup> pregnancy and she is in her 15<sup>th</sup> week. As she has the risk of Trisomy again, you advised her to undergo a test for karyotyping. What is the test you advise her considering the gestational age?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q1929696",
