      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A mother brings her 7-months-old child to the clinic with a history of developmental delays, Failure to thrive, and anomaly shown in the image. On further evaluation he has a small head circumference, low-set ears, small mouth and clenched hands with overlapping fingers. Additional findings of heart murmur and scoliosis were also noted. The physician suspects it to be case of Trisomy based on the clinical findings, What is the Karyotype finding is seen in this case?</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/03/15/picture17.jpg\" style=\"height:363px; width:250px\" /></span></span></p>",
